/or anonymized data with others for their own uses.</span></li></ul><h4 class="c3" id="h.krgca3qpwn4f"><span class="c7">3. INTERNATIONAL TRANSFER</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">The Company has offices inside the EU and has affiliates and service providers in other countries. Your personal information may be transferred to other locations outside of your state, province, country or other governmental jurisdiction where privacy laws may not be as protective as those in your jurisdiction.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">EU users should read the important information provided below about transfer of personal information outside of the European Economic Area (EEA).</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.qew4042uj3c0"><span class="c7">4. HOW INFORMATION IS SECURED</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We retain information we collect as long as it is necessary and relevant to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy. In addition, we retain personal information to comply with applicable law where required, prevent fraud, resolve disputes, troubleshoot problems, assist with any investigation, enforce our Terms of Use, and other actions permitted by law. To determine the appropriate retention period for personal information, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal information, the potential risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of your personal information, the purposes for which we process your personal information and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">In some circumstances we may anonymize your personal information (so that it can no longer be associated with you) in which case we may use this information indefinitely without further notice to you.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We employ industry standard security measures designed to protect the security of all information submitted through the Services. However, the security of information transmitted through the internet can never be guaranteed. We are not responsible for any interception or interruption of any communications through the internet or for changes to or losses of data. Users of the Services are responsible for maintaining the security of any password, user identification or other form of authentication involved in obtaining access to password protected or secure areas of any of our digital services.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.6va8ms4ur8qc"><span class="c7">5. RECIPIENTS</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">The files are stored in our Web storage providers, shipping management, email and online marketing, in accordance with the EU Privacy security:</span></p><ul class="c5 lst-kix_wb7jystzkk56-0 start"><li class="c0 c6"><span class="c1">List of places where we keep information:</span></li><li class="c0 c6"><span class="c1">OVH (EU)</span></li><li class="c0 c6"><span class="c1">Contabo (EU)</span></li></ul><p class="c0"><span class="c1">By accepting this Privacy Policy, you expressly authorize us to treat and communicate your personal data to possible companies or foundations linked to us and / or to transfer your personal data to the referred service providers as treatment managers located for the purposes described here and to give you a complete service.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Creativechain FND expressly informs and guarantees users that their personal data will not be transferred in any case to third companies and that, whenever some type of personal data transfer was to be made, prior consent would be requested, informed, and unmistakable by the owners.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.lsk729nblan9"><span class="c7">6. RIGHT OF ACCESS, RECTIFICATION, OPPOSITION AND CANCELLATION</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">In order to exercise your rights of access, rectification, opposition or cancellation, you can access the information you have voluntarily provided through your account in the Services, and review, correct or eliminate it by sending a request to privacy@onecomet.co . You can request to change the contact options, choose not to share it with other people and update your information and personal preferences. We can demand that you be the user that you say you are by proving that you have control of your publication key through our transport API.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Likewise, you may choose not to receive direct marketing communications that you have previously agreed to receive. We may continue to send you Service-related and other non-marketing communications.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.zr7a5u3iaop"><span class="c7">7. CONTACT INFORMATION</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Your comments or questions about this Policy are welcome, and you can contact us at: privacy@onecomet.co.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We may change this privacy policy at any time. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices. If we make any changes, we will change the Last Updated date above and we will inform you of the existence of the changes, so that you can conveniently review them.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Any modifications to this Privacy Policy will be effective upon our posting of the new terms and/or upon implementation of the changes to the Site (or as otherwise indicated at the time of posting). In all cases, your continued use of the the Site or Services after the posting of any modified Privacy Policy indicates your acceptance of the terms of the modified Privacy Policy.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.clr3mbxxb36"><span class="c7">8. ELIGIBILITY</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">If you are under the age of majority in your jurisdiction of residence, you may use the Services only with the consent of or under the supervision of your parent or legal guardian. Consistent with the requirements of the RGDP, if we learn that we have received any information directly from a child without first receiving his or her parent\'s verified consent, we will use that information only to respond directly to that child (or his or her parent or legal guardian) to inform the child that he or she cannot use the Site and subsequently we will delete that information.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.fmdp6qqosu57"><span class="c7">9. COOKIES POLICY</span></h4><h4 class="c3" id="h.tph5ft3jhm90"><span class="c4">WHAT IS A COOKIE?</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">A cookie is a small text file that is downloaded to your computer\'s browser, mobile phone, tablet or any other Internet access device when you visit a website.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.q13n4r1iiukk"><span class="c4">WHAT ARE THEY FOR?</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Cookies are used to recognize the device when you return to visit the website, facilitating its use when remembering your preferences and navigation settings (eg language, country, access data, etc.). They also provide certain functionalities (eg, display ads related to the content of the pages you visit, avoid showing you continuously announcements that you have already seen, etc.), and allow us to collect anonymous statistical information about the user’s site navigation.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">There are other technologies such as pixel tags ("pixel tags"), web bugs ("web bugs"), web storage and other similar files and technologies that can also perform the same function as cookies. We use the term "cookie" to refer to all similar technologies that collect information in this way.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">The cookies do not store any personal data, nor any type of information that can identify you, and they are useful and important because they allow the web to work in an agile way and adapted to your preferences.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.nh1uif1mwg1v"><span class="c4">WHY DO WE USE COOKIES?</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We generally use cookies for the following purposes:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">To allow registered users to stay connected to the site after they close their browser window.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">To store user preferences for site functionality.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">To track the use of the site so we can improve our site and better understand how people are using it.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">To better understand the interests of our users and visitors to our website.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Some Cookies are necessary for certain uses of the Site, and without such Cookies, we would not be able to provide many services that you need to properly use the Site. These Cookies, for example, allow us to operate our Site so you may access it as you have requested and let us recognize that you have created an account and have logged into that account to access Site content. They also include Cookies that enable us to remember your previous actions within the same browsing session and secure our Sites.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We also use functional Cookies and Cookies from third parties for analysis and marketing purposes. Functional Cookies enable certain parts of the site to work properly and your user preferences to remain known. Analysis Cookies, among other things, collect information on how visitors use our Site, the content and products that users view most frequently, and the effectiveness of our third party advertising. Advertising Cookies assist in delivering ads to relevant audiences and having our ads appear at the top of search results. Cookies are either "session" Cookies which are deleted when you end your browser session, or "persistent," which remains until their deletion by you (discussed below) or the party who served the cookie. Full details on all of the Cookies used on the Site are available at our Cookie Disclosure table below.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.pkrtthkcle4q"><span class="c4">HOW TO DISABLE COOKIES?.</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">You can generally activate or later deactivate the use of cookies through a functionality built into your web browser. To learn more about how to control cookie settings through your browser:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c8"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1575475480197000">Click here</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;to learn more about the “Private Browsing” setting and managing cookie settings in Firefox:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c8"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl%3Den&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1575475480198000">Click here</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;to learn more about the “Private Browsing” setting and managing cookie settings in Chrome:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c8"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/17442/windows-internet-explorer-delete-manage-cookies&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1575475480200000">Click here</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;to learn more about the “Private Browsing” setting and managing cookie settings in Internet Explorer:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c8"><a class="c9" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://support.apple.com/kb/ph21411?locale%3Den_US&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1575475480201000">Click here</a></span><span class="c1">&nbsp;to learn more about the “Private Browsing” setting and managing cookie settings in Safari:</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">If you want to learn more about cookies, or how to control, disable or delete them, please visit http://www.aboutcookies.org for detailed guidance. In addition, certain third party advertising networks, including Google, permit users to opt out of or customize preferences associated with your internet browsing.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">We may link the information collected by Cookies with other information we collect from you to this Privacy Policy and use the combined information as set forth herein. Similarly, the third parties who serve cookies on our Site may link your name or email address to other information they collect, which may include past purchases made offline or online, or your online usage information. If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have certain rights that are described above under the heading "Notice to EU Data Subjects", including the right to inspect and correct or delete the data that we have about you.</span></p><h4 class="c3" id="h.j7ij2nk3c0h5"><span class="c4">TYPES OF COOKIES THAT WE USE</span></h4><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Preference cookies</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">They allow the user to access the Service with some predefined general characteristics based on a series of criteria in the user\'s device. These cookies allow us to know if you have visited our website before. They keep your preferences for certain tools or services so you do not have to configure the website every time you visit us. They retain user navigation preferences, such as language, browser type or aesthetic elements of the content.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Registration and session cookies</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">These cookies keep the necessary information during the session and the changes related to it, and determine if you are registered or not on the web. They are used to identify your user account. These cookies are kept as long as you do not leave the session, close the browser or turn off the device.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Geolocation cookies.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">These cookies, by third parties, are used by programs that try to identify geographically the location of the device from which the user is connected (computer, smartphone, tablet, etc.), to offer anonymous content and services that best suit his location .</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Third party cookies of this type on our website: Google Analytics, Google Adwords, Twitter and Facebook.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Analytic cookies.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">These cookies allow quantifying the number of visitors and statistically analyze the browsing of users through our website always anonymously.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Third party cookies of this type on our website: Google Analytics, Google Adwords, Twitter and Facebook.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Advertising cookies</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">They allow the management, in the most efficient way possible, of the advertising spaces that, if applicable, the editor has included in a website, application or platform from which the requested service is provided. These cookies store information on the behavior of users obtained through the continuous observation of their browsing habits, which allows the development of a specific profile to display advertising based on it.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Third party cookies of this type on our website: Google Adwords and Facebook.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Social network cookies</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">They are used so that visitors can interact with the content of different social platforms (Facebook, YouTube, Twitter, etc.) and that they are generated only for the users of these social networks. The conditions of use of these cookies and the information collected is regulated by the privacy policy of the corresponding social platform.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">Third party cookies of this type on our website: Twitter, Facebook, Google +, LinkedIn, Pinterest.</span></p><p class="c0 c11"><span class="c1"></span></p>'
